                        <textLang mainLang="ota">Ottoman Turkish</textLang>
                        <msItem xml:id="MS_Greaves_36-item1" n="1">
                            <title key="work_23408">Rūznāme-yi Ḥażret-i Şeyḫ Vefā</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ota" key="work_23408">روزنامهٔ حضرت شيخ وفا</title>
                            <author key="person_34377777">
                                <persName xml:lang="ota-Latn-x-lc">Şeyḫ Vefā</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="ota">شیخ وفا</persName>
                                <lb></lb>
                                <persName xml:lang="ota-Latn-x-lc">Muṣṭafā bin Aḥmed aṣ-Ṣadrī el-Künevī</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="ota">مصطفی بن احمد الصدری الکنوی</persName>
                            </author>
                            <note>NOTE: This record has been automatically generated with minimal
                                modification from the corresponding entry in a printed catalogue. It
                                may contain errors. Please, consult the References section below for
                                more information.</note>
                            <note>The perpetual calendar of Şeyḫ Vefā, i. e. Muṣṭafā bin Aḥmed
                                aṣ-Ṣadrī el-Künevī, called Musliḥuddīn Vefā, who flourished in the
                                reign of Sulṭān Muḥammed II (AH 855-886=AD 1451-1481) and died AH
                                896=AD 1491, in that of Sulṭān Bāyezīd II (AH 886-918=AD 1481-1512),
                                see Rieu, pp. 122 and 123. G. Flügel ii. pp. 247 and 493 sq. wrongly
                                ascribes this calendar to the author of the history of the campaigns
                                of Sulṭān Murad III (تواريخ غزوات سلطان مراد ثالث), Şeyḫ Muḥammed
                                Vefā or Vefā'ī, who flourished about AH 994=AD 1586; see Rieu's
                                remarks on this point and Fleischer, Cat. Lips., p. 432a, where a
                                copy of the روزنامه, with the date AH 954 AD 1547 is noticed; comp.
                                also Krafft, pp. 141 and 142; J. Aumer, p. 66; G. Flügel iii. pp.
                                519 and 545; and W. Pertsch, Berlin Cat., p. 193 (No. 172, which,
                                although described without an author's name, is quite identical with
                                our present روزنامه), and G. H. Velschius: Commentarius in Ruzname
                                Naurus sive tabulae aequinoctiales novi Persarum et Turcicarum
                                anni,' Augsburg, 1576, in which an engraved facsimile of Şeyḫ Vefā's
                                روزنامه has been published. This copy, agreeing with No. 172 in the
                                Berlin Collection and No. 1426 in the Vienna Library, begins with
                                two chronological circles, the دائره نوروز سلطانی and the دائرة
                                كبيسا (or rather کبیسه, the circle of the leap-year), see pp. 4 and
                                5 of the Turkish text in the edition of Velschius; after which
                                follow the tables of the twelve Syrian months, commencing with ماه
                                آذر, arranged exactly as the first Vienna copy.</note>
